meta.description: Delta Air Lines Delta Sky Club at Hartsfield–Jackson Atlanta International Airport (ATL), Concourse E. Learn more about the lounge: amenities, photos, review, opening hours, location.

lounge.name: Delta Air Lines Delta Sky Club
lounge.description: The Delta Sky Club is an award-winning retreat that allows relaxation, productivity, or both.

reviews.content: Grossly disappointing lounge. Should be rated basic. Went to the Club at ATL...virtually the same food...maybe better there. More space but many broken power outlets here. Extremely crowded.
Not crowded at all at 8 pm on a Monday night. Very large lounge with plenty of separate spaces to sit and find a quiet place. Decent food area.
Overcrowded, poor Wi-Fi connection, probably due to the mass of people trying to get on. Find a seat & you could probably sell it to highest bidder. Food looked marginal, picked over, bar 3 ppl deep.
Terrible lounge not worth visiting. Waste of money and time. Cheap on food and drink.
I haven’t been to a lot of lounges but this isn’t that nice of an experience. Free alcohol is limited to a few rail liquors. Food is OK, also limited - salad & pastas. No free guests either...at all.
Probably due to the fact that it’s situated near the international gates, but this is the best Delta Lounge I’ve been in.  Spacious, SPA, showers, and a plethora of private and common areas!
Great food and lots of space on a Sunday afternoon.
Spacious longer with some more quiet, dimly lit areas. Spa services are available along with showers. Food selection is good and full service bar.
Not well stocked. Breakfast area was messy. Very crowded. Skipped D to go here and wasn’t worth it.
This place is poor for a gateway city. I can’t remember a less interesting lounge in the USA. It’s like the place for everyone with coach seats and lounge access.
While the Delta lounge in concourse B is the “flagship” for Atlanta, I think the club in E has more room and is less crowded.
The lounge has a great look to it. Was here during breakfast which was lacklustre. Hard biscuits, and very few options.
Pleasant and comfortable. Nice hot breakfast spread.
Stopped by on a Tuesday morning. Wasn’t too crowded, had quite a nice food spread, and decent assortment of seats. Not bad!
Busy lounge but spacious and this Sky Lounge has showers so if you have time it's worth the visit. Decent food selection and full service bar. Be patient during peak times as this place can fill up.
Visited the E Terminal Sky Club and would say it's on par with the other Sky Clubs in ATL.  Decent food. Nice dark quiet room (except somebody decided to make it their phone call room). Showers.
Staff spends too much time chatting with each other than replenishing supplies.
Great layover stop for a shower, quick snack. Lots of space to relax/lay down. Was not busy at 0700 on a Wed morning.

This is a nice lounge. The food was excellent and it is right in line with Delta quality. My only two points of contention are the bathrooms were in bad shape because of the crowding and it was crowded.
Very nice showers. Great food. Friendly staff.
Quiet, hidden, and comfortable!
Delta made some major upgrades this year 2015. I notice more food options and a faster wifi connection.
Clean showers and bathroom. The food, wine, and cocktail selection is good. Worth a trip in if convenient.
Certainly large, but an example of Delta's cheap-looking "space age" circa-2010 motif. Just not pretty. Good and typical SC snack and drink options. Certainly better than the E terminal public areas.
This is easily one of the nicest in the US. Has lots of open spaces and color coordination.
This is a huge lounge. Plenty of seating and very bright. Both times I went it was morning, they have a small but sufficient buffet, and there's a bartender at 7am. Yes please.
Extremely crowded with few seats available. Snack options were pitiful. WiFi iffy. Complimentary Sweetwater IPA and nice views are only good aspects.
Early Monday AM not crowded, reasonable selection of breakfast options. Comfortable seating options and lots of power outlets.
Great showers and plenty of room.
E lounge pretty nice, showers, mult seating areas, quiet room, lots of glass, and big bar.
Large comfortable room, different spaces to stay. Apron view. Nice for breakfast, but poor during the day. Most alcoholic beverages or drinks are charged.
There are good showers in this lounge, but very few snacks are offered.
This is a huge lounge with lots of private seating. The big luxury bar also has lots of snacks.
